  <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color:#684182;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BLOOD PRESSURE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</text>
</STATIC_heading>
  </block>
  <block refid="342bfd2c-7b64-4c84-ac80-c810f9e086c6">
    <STATIC_text>
  <text>&lt;p&gt;Blood pressure is the force that the blood exerts on the arterial walls. This pressure is measured with a &lt;strong&gt;sphygmomanometer&lt;/strong&gt; (Figure 11-11).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The sphygmomanometer consists of a rubber bag inside a cloth cuff that is wrapped around the upper arm, just above the elbow. The rubber bag is inflated with air using a handbulb pump. As the bag is pumped up, the pressure within it increases and is measured on a recording device attached to the cuff.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
</STATIC_text>
  </block>
